<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b2903-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10303"><num value="10303">§ 10303.</num><heading> Provisions</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68b2904-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10303/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A seaman shall be served at least 3 meals a day that total at least 3,100 calories, including adequate water and adequate protein, vitamins, and minerals in accordance with the United States Recommended Daily Allowances.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68b2905-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10303/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The text of subsection (a) of this section shall be included in the agreement required by <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s10302">section 10302 of this title</ref>. A copy of the text also shall be posted in a conspicuous place in the galley and forecastle of each vessel.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68b2906-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10303/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content> This section does not apply to a fishing or whaling vessel or a yacht.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf68b2907-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/562">97 Stat. 562</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
